  Title: God in All Worlds
  Locus:
    Page: 63
  Source:
    Title: New Seeds of Contemplation
By: Thomas Merton
---
Souls are like wax waiting for a seal. By themselves they have no special
identity. The wax that has melted in God's will can easily receive the stamp
of its identity, the truth of what it was meant to be.
